# Zero-Knowledge Verification

ExactPay uses Zero-Knowledge (ZK) technology to transform identity verification into a reusable digital credential.

Instead of repeatedly submitting identity documents to multiple financial service providers, users verify their identity once. A Zero-Knowledge proof allows participating services to verify eligibility without exposing the user's underlying personal information.

## Objectives

- Verify Once, Reuse Anywhere
- Preserve user privacy
- Reduce repeated KYC processes
- Enable portable financial identity

## Planned Workflow

Identity Verification
        ↓
Generate ZK Proof
        ↓
Reusable Digital Credential
        ↓
Financial Service Verification
        ↓
Payment Authorization

## Future Scope

The prototype is designed to support modern Zero-Knowledge proof systems such as Noir, Circom, or other compatible proving frameworks as the platform evolves.

The focus of ExactPay is not to showcase Zero-Knowledge technology itself, but to use it to deliver a simpler and more seamless financial experience.
